{"info": {"author": "cdlr75", "author_email": "cdlr75@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Topic :: Software Development :: Build Tools"], "description": "# Status\n[![PEP8](https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-pep8-green.svg)](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008/)\n[![coverage report](https://gitlab.com/cdlr75/status/badges/master/coverage.svg)](https://gitlab.com/cdlr75/status/-/commits/master)\n\n\nSimple way to make a /status for your services with python and asyncio.\n\n## Install\n\n```sh\npip install api-status\n```\n\n## How it works ?\n\n**TL;DR;**\n\nCheck a working example at:\nhttps://gitlab.com/cdlr75/status/-/blob/develop/tests/learning/example.py\n\n\nLet say you have a coroutine that replies a dict with the desired status of your service:\n```py\nasync def status():\n    \"\"\" Returns our service status.\n\n    :returns: Misc info about our service.\n    :rtype: dict\n    \"\"\"\n    return {\n        \"name\": \"MyService\",\n        \"status\": \"ok\",\n        \"version\": \"v1\"\n    }\n```\nWith *api-status*, to expose this through an HTTP endpoint:\n```py\nfrom status import Server\n\nserver = Server(host=\"127.0.0.1\", port=8080)\n# register our status endpoint\nserver.add_route(status, method=\"GET\", path=r\"/status\")\nawait server.start()\n# the status is now available at http://127.0.0.1:8080/status\n```\nIf you take care of graceful shutdowns for your services, call the method `stop`:\n```py\nawait server.stop()\n```\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://gitlab.com/pypa/sampleproject", "keywords": "api status service", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "api-status", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/api-status/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/api-status/", "project_urls": {"Bug Reports": "https://gitlab.com/cdlr75/status/issues", "Homepage": "https://gitlab.com/pypa/sampleproject", "Source": "https://gitlab.com/cdlr75/status/"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/api-status/1.0.1/", "requires_dist": ["aiohttp (>=3.5)", "sphinx ; extra == 'doc'", "recommonmark ; extra == 'doc'", "changelogfromtags ; extra == 'doc'", "pytest ; extra == 'test'", "pytest-cov ; extra == 'test'", "asynctest ; extra == 'test'", "pycodestyle ; extra == 'test'", "pylint ; extra == 'test'"], "requires_python": ">=3.6", "summary": "Simple way to make a /status for your services with python and asyncio.", "version": "1.0.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Status</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"PEP8\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/6fb00dfb51e9ef50800acf286dab4c6c7b018f5b/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f636f64652532307374796c652d706570382d677265656e2e737667\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://gitlab.com/cdlr75/status/-/commits/master\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"coverage report\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/dc3e4bd0dfac220ba219adf6ee0facdf49f523e7/68747470733a2f2f6769746c61622e636f6d2f63646c7237352f7374617475732f6261646765732f6d61737465722f636f7665726167652e737667\"></a></p>\n<p>Simple way to make a /status for your services with python and asyncio.</p>\n<h2>Install</h2>\n<pre>pip install api-status\n</pre>\n<h2>How it works ?</h2>\n<p><strong>TL;DR;</strong></p>\n<p>Check a working example at:\n<a href=\"https://gitlab.com/cdlr75/status/-/blob/develop/tests/learning/example.py\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://gitlab.com/cdlr75/status/-/blob/develop/tests/learning/example.py</a></p>\n<p>Let say you have a coroutine that replies a dict with the desired status of your service:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"k\">async</span> <span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">status</span><span class=\"p\">():</span>\n    <span class=\"sd\">\"\"\" Returns our service status.</span>\n\n<span class=\"sd\">    :returns: Misc info about our service.</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">    :rtype: dict</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">    \"\"\"</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"s2\">\"name\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"MyService\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"s2\">\"status\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"ok\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"s2\">\"version\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"v1\"</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</pre>\n<p>With <em>api-status</em>, to expose this through an HTTP endpoint:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">status</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">Server</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">server</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Server</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">host</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"127.0.0.1\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">port</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">8080</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"c1\"># register our status endpoint</span>\n<span class=\"n\">server</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">add_route</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">status</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"GET\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"sa\">r</span><span class=\"s2\">\"/status\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"k\">await</span> <span class=\"n\">server</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">start</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"c1\"># the status is now available at http://127.0.0.1:8080/status</span>\n</pre>\n<p>If you take care of graceful shutdowns for your services, call the method <code>stop</code>:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"k\">await</span> <span class=\"n\">server</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">stop</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6626141, "releases": {"1.0.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "dfe39e7db15c6b85959dc7a0b12d1861", "sha256": "9a1c5c75aee14656732fb42a3a4fa21a3dc0a795cd0c4de6e539fdcac2e876bd"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "api_status-1.0.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "dfe39e7db15c6b85959dc7a0b12d1861", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.6", "size": 8473, "upload_time": "2020-02-13T14:20:32", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-13T14:20:32.306552Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/69/62/af7127fa279f1f22b39a380cf2922404fc24dc8f3d2eff3a6831347ed008/api_status-1.0.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "e6effae33538a2b3e90bc75fc15b50d0", "sha256": "c2ff8e4f028e0e9a36b624dd0e9e393371455b3fdadf405d049093b5cae7ab12"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "api-status-1.0.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "e6effae33538a2b3e90bc75fc15b50d0", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.6", "size": 10458, "upload_time": "2020-02-13T14:20:34", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-13T14:20:34.472569Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/b8/e6/ffc438f5388b7689db9aec6277b79c5e739060ba0158a05c896f706d16bf/api-status-1.0.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "1.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "f67ac03fcf1b1ba61282207cb543dc64", "sha256": "54e8a47251dcdb90e2685cfa0be31015adc9